Jeremy Clarkson&#039;s Motorworld was a BBC television series about the car and motoring cultures of various different countries. The show was presented by Jeremy Clarkson and consisted of two series of six episodes each plus a special focussing on the UK. Each individual episode focussed on a different country or region.

The series was first shown in the UK on BBC Two in 1995, and was subsequently shown to an international audience on BBC World.

The Best Of Jeremy Clarkson&#039;s Motorworld, a video containing 70 minutes of highlights from the series was released on October 7 1996. The video was later released on DVD, as part of The Jeremy Clarkson Collection in 2007. There was also a book written by Clarkson based on the series.
